        "product_description": {
            "value": "The ASR Outdoor Gold Panning Classifier Screens are a must-have for gold prospecting and mineral recovery. Using high-impact steel wire classifier sieves is one of the first steps in successful gold prospecting. These classifier soil sifting screens allow you to increase the amount of material you can run by separating unwanted coarse raw material into finer, manageable material ready to wash in your gold pan or run through a sluice box. This 1/70\" mesh screen features 4900 holes per inch for fine material classification. Constructed from tough, high-impact ABS plastic and 304 stainless steel wire mesh with a reinforced high side wall, each screen fits over a standard 5 gallon bucket as well as a 14\" gold pan. The stackable, interlocking design ensures they will not slip or slide when used together. Top Diameter: 13.25\", Bottom Diameter: 11\". Proper classification of material by size is the key to more efficient gold separation, from roughing out your material to the final step of fine gold separation. Using a sieve works for panning, sluicing and high banking equally well. Screening or classifying material into groups based on size ensures that any gold, whether nuggets or flakes, will not get lost. Separating and processing your gold concentrates by size with a classifier makes gold recovery much more efficient and less labor intensive, speeding up the panning process and resulting in more gold. Ideal for many different purposes and a wide range of materials.",
            "is_required": true,
            "source": "ai",
